# Why: Documenso (Remix + Hono) ships with no server-side error tracking.
#      Errors that happen on the server are logged to stdout (now also
#      to Axiom via overlay's log drain) but there's no error-aggregation
#      surface — no grouping, no alerts, no stack traces with source maps,
#      no per-error trend.
#
#      Browser-side errors are already captured by PostHog (see
#      apps/remix/app/entry.client.tsx:24 — `capture_exceptions: true`).
#      The gap is purely server-side.
#
#      Solution: add `@sentry/node` and initialize it as the very first
#      module loaded by the server entry point (main.js). Sentry's docs
#      require this ordering — the SDK hooks Node's process-level
#      exception/rejection handlers and the HTTP module, which only
#      works if no other modules have loaded those first.
#
#      Sibling product CircularPay already uses Sentry (@sentry/nextjs
#      ^10.48.0) so adding @sentry/node ^10.48.0 to Pacta means both
#      products share an SDK major version, which simplifies stack-trace
#      symbolication and any shared utilities later.
#
#      Files added:
#        - apps/remix/server/instrument.mjs
#          Sentry init module. Side-effect-only — exports nothing. Init
#          runs only when NEXT_PRIVATE_SENTRY_DSN is set AND
#          NODE_ENV=production. Includes a `beforeSend` PII scrubber
#          that strips query strings (signing tokens), cookies, and
#          authorization headers — critical for fintech hygiene.
#
#      Files patched:
#        - apps/remix/server/main.js
#          Adds `import './instrument.mjs'` as the first import so the
#          SDK initializes before any other module loads.
#        - apps/remix/.bin/build.sh
#          Adds `cp server/instrument.mjs build/server/instrument.mjs`
#          so the file lands next to main.js in the production build.
#          Same verbatim-copy pattern as main.js (no compilation).
#        - apps/remix/package.json
#          Adds `"@sentry/node": "^10.48.0"` to dependencies.
#
#      No client-side Sentry: PostHog already captures browser errors
#      via `capture_exceptions: true`. Adding @sentry/react would
#      double-capture and bloat the client bundle. Defer until/unless
#      we want full session-replay capability (which we explicitly
#      decided against — Pacta's audit trail is the primary forensic
#      record).
#
#      Operator config (manual, post-deploy):
#        1. Sentry UI → create project `pacta-platform`, platform: Node.js
#        2. Copy DSN
#        3. Coolify → Pacta backend → Environment Variables → add
#           NEXT_PRIVATE_SENTRY_DSN=<paste>
#        4. Restart container (env var only — no rebuild needed)
#        5. Verify: trigger a test error, observe in Sentry within 30s
#
#      Source maps: not uploaded. Stack traces will show minified names.
#      Future v2: add SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN env var + sentry-cli upload step
#      in build.sh for readable traces. Same trade-off CircularPay made
#      (see ~/github/bizrethink/client-circular-payments-platform/
#      next.config.mjs — `sourcemaps: { disable: true }`).
#
#      Fragility:
#        LOW for instrument.mjs and build.sh — new file + one-line append.
#        LOW for main.js — single import added at the top, comment makes
#        the ordering requirement obvious for future-me.
#        LOW for package.json — additive dep, no removals.
#
#      Long-term: file an upstream Documenso issue suggesting they add
#      opt-in Sentry support via env var (DOCUMENSO_SENTRY_DSN). Self-
#      hosters running fintech/healthcare/regulated apps universally
#      need this; baking it in saves every operator from re-implementing
#      this overlay.
